{"id":3288,"date":"2017-03-08T14:44:03","date_gmt":"2017-03-08T12:44:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/?p=3288"},"modified":"2017-03-08T14:44:03","modified_gmt":"2017-03-08T12:44:03","slug":"git-clean-remove-all-local-branches","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/2017\/03\/git-clean-remove-all-local-branches\/","title":{"rendered":"git-clean: Remove all local branches"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Made a <a href=\"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/2013\/04\/%D1%83%D0%B4%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%82%D1%8C-%D0%B2%D1%81%D0%B5-%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%BB%D1%8C%D0%BD%D1%8B%D0%B5-%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%BA%D0%B8-git\/\">note<\/a> about it 4 years ago, but it looks like the note\u00a0is still pretty usefull. So one more time for en readers.<\/p>\n<p>To remove all merged branches(except current -v &#8216;*&#8217;):<\/p>\n<pre>git branch --merged | grep -v '*' | xargs git branch -D\r\n<\/pre>\n<p>also I made such command for repo complete clean up:<\/p>\n<pre>alias git-clean=\"git branch  | grep -v '*' | grep -v 'master' | xargs git branch -D  &amp;&amp; git reset --hard &amp;&amp; git clean -d -x -f\"\r\n<\/pre>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Made a note about it 4 years ago, but it looks like the note\u00a0is still pretty usefull. So one more time for en readers. To remove all merged branches(except current -v &#8216;*&#8217;): git branch &#8211;merged | grep -v &#8216;*&#8217; | &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/2017\/03\/git-clean-remove-all-local-branches\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[71,467],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3288"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/stepansuvorov.com\/blog\/wp